According to a report by Intel Market Research, the global molybdenum market was valued at USD 3.42 billion in 2025 and is projected to grow from USD 3.61 billion in 2026 to USD 5.18 billion by 2034, registering a CAGR of 4.7% during the forecast period. The market is witnessing sustained growth due to rising demand for high-strength steel, increasing investments in infrastructure, expanding renewable energy projects, and the growing adoption of molybdenum-based alloys in aerospace, automotive, and advanced manufacturing industries. As industries continue to prioritize durable, corrosion-resistant, and high-performance materials, molybdenum is becoming an increasingly strategic metal for next-generation industrial applications.
